<h1>Problem 249 - 2011 All-Russian MO, Grade 10, Day 1, P4 of 4, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Triangle \(ABC\) has perimeter \(4\). Points \(X\) and \(Y\) are on rays \(AB\) and \(AC\) respectively such that \(AX=AY=1\). Segments \(BC\) and \(XY\) intersect at \(M\). Prove that the perimeter of either triangle \(ABM\) or \(ACM\) is 2.</p>
